The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Santiniketan, May 13: Visva-Bharati today conferred the Deshikottama on actor Soumitra Chatterjee and dance maestro Birju Maharaj at its convocation.

 Governor Gopal Krishna Gandhi, who is the rector of the university, made a traditional presentation of chhatim leaves to the students at the programme held at Amrakunja, around 195 km from Calcutta. He also visited Natun Bari on the university campus where Mahatma Gandhi had stayed for a week during his first visit to Santiniketan in 1915.

 Behrampore: Nine CPM workers were injured in a string of clashes in Jangipur and Behrampore, about 250 km from Calcutta. No arrests have been made but police are on vigil in the disturbed areas. A member of the CPMs Murshidabad district secretariat, Mriganka Bhattacharya, alleged that Congress activists had attacked the CPM workers.

 Durgapur: The father of seven-year-old Munni Bharti, who has been missing since Thursday, has lodged a police complaint saying he has been receiving ransom calls from Gaya in Bihar. A police team has left for Gaya. Munni, a Class II student, went missing on her way back home from school.

 Calcutta: Sambhu Mondal, 35, was shot dead at Mograhat on the southern fringes of the city on Saturday. Police said Sambhu was first hit by a sharp weapon before being shot from close range.




